  "abstract": {
    "value": "Chiral allenyl phosphine oxides represent a significant kind of synthetic target with promising potential for various applications. However, explorations toward their asymmetric synthesis remain scarce, primarily due to the competitive coordination of phosphine oxides with metal catalysts. Herein, we report a Pd-catalyzed enantioselective allenylation of secondary phosphine oxide for the eficient construction of a variety of chiral allenyl phosphine oxides. The success of this reaction arises from the enhanced (bidentate form) coordination of a newly designed, fungicide-inspired enyne-type propargylic carbamate with a chiral Pd complex. This protocol features high yields and enantioselectivities, scalability, and versatile derivatization. Mechanistic studies confirmed the exclusion of a kinetic resolution pathway.",
    "source": "content_list_inline_abstract",
